    "body": "## Problem\r\n`vim.net.transport`'s logging is tied to LSP logging.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nParameterize the `vim.Log` object so that we can log in files other than `lsp.log`.\r\n\r\nLater, we can separate logs for different LSP servers into multiple files (e.g., `lua_ls` in `logs/lsp/luals.log`) so that their stderr can be recorded separately.\r\n\r\n#38525 requires this; I separate here so that we can share ideas on the improvements for LSP logging.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Later, we can separate logs for different LSP servers into multiple files (e.g., `lua_ls` in `logs/lsp/luals.log`) so that their stderr can be recorded separately.\n\nLove this idea. We could also add a `log_level` field to `vim.lsp.ClientConfig` so log levels can adjusted separately for each log file.",
